    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2006-05-04</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2006-05-26T19:39:17Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Research Competitiveness Act of 2006 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to: (1) modify the tax credit for increasing research expenses to establish a standard 20% credit rate for research expenses exceeding 50% of average expenses over the preceding three year period; (2) establish a uniform 80% reimbursement rate for all contract research expenses (100% for basic research payments); (3) make such tax credit permanent; (4) allow a tax credit for equity investments in small business innovation companies; and (5) allow the issuance of tax exempt facility bonds for research park facilities used in connection with research and experimentation.</p><p>Directs the Secretary of the Treasury to issue regulations on the application of private activity bond rules to the funding of federal research agreements.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
